entries.femaleVariant: Is that you, V? Or…
[Pet cat] Who's this?
Who do we have here, huh?
That's Mr. Brightman.
Yeah, it's me.
OK, I'm ready.
[Lean] Let's do it.
Since you have to wait, mind if I give you a reading?
Like Vik said. Taken matters into my own hands.
So, what now?
Waitin' for my driver.
Come inside. We'll wait together.
Only if you want.
Sure.
Rather not.
Sure, why not.
I devised this layout especially for you and Johnny.
Y'know... prolly not a good idea.
We found the poor guy in the trash behind the clinic.
I think he misses Jackie.
Ain't alone.
Your future is his future... and vice versa.
Hm. I think that's for you.
Wait, is that... an Arasaka stretch?
But... V! They killed Jackie! And-- and now you're working for them?!
That's right.
Alternatives were worse.
Jackie died because we both made a bad decision.
Don't like it any more than you do, but all the other options were worse.
Still don't get it, do you?
entries.maleVariant: Still don't get it, do ya?

entries.femaleVariant: Jackie died 'cause we made a terrible fucking decision.
And the rest – just plain consequences.
Time to make things right.
Misty, listen...
Betraying a friend – you can't justify that.
Think I don't remember?
Got no right to judge me.
You've changed… For the worse.
Lovely little shithole...
So, this is where Arasaka's finest technology wound up... Charming.
V, it's good to meet again. You look…
Like shit.
And I feel like shit.
Compared to you, sure.
Compared to you, I do. You look good.
I am back in graces, as you say.
Feel like shit. And it's gettin' worse.
entries.maleVariant: I feel like shit. And it's gettin' worse.

entries.femaleVariant: Yeah, just foretold I'd break your jaw.
Yeah, but I can tell you where to put your suspicions.
Let us go to the car. Hanako-sama is waiting.
Where's the ripper? Telling fortunes from rat bones in the back?
Anders Hellman. Alive. What a surprise.
That's right. Matter of fact, just foretold I'd break your shit-spewing jaw.
Anders Hellman. Alive, I see, and well.
Figured your employers woulda knocked you around some after your flight to Kang Tao.
entries.maleVariant: Figured your employers would've knocked you around some after your flight to Kang Tao.

entries.femaleVariant: 'Member the last time I did that, I trust.
You look after yourself, V.
Hmm. I think that's for you.
Whatever you prefer. Perhaps it's best.
Yep. No mistakin' that ride, ever.
Hey.
You scared me, you know that?
Jesus, you really do look terrible.
The construct in your head and how it could affect decision-making.
The same construct that, in its former life, detonated two nuclear warheads inside Arasaka Tower.
And now you and this construct have volunteered to sort things out in Arasaka.
Interesting coincidence, wouldn't you say?
When we last saw one another, we spoke of a construct in your head that could influence your decision-making.
The same construct that, in its former life, detonated two nuclear warheads inside Arasaka Tower.
What is this about?
Has no one told you? Shame.
The engram inside is Johnny-fucking-Silverhand. Recognize the name?
Johnny's my problem, not yours.
Yes, but he's suppressed now.
With beta-blockers. But before I did that, he warned me against working with Arasaka.
So tuck your suspicions where the sun don't shine before I start regretting not taking his advice.
That is enough for me.
Johnny's my concern, not yours.
The terrorist?
Johnny's blocked off. And I bear no ill will against Arasaka.
Not nearly as interesting as your paranoia.
Aren't you just my driver? Do your fuckin' job.
Think you might be outta line, Hellman.
Hanako appointed you my chauffeur.
It is, but not nearly as interesting as your paranoia.
Got Johnny in check with beta-blockers. And Arasaka's not on my radar.
entries.maleVariant: I got Johnny in check with beta-blockers. And Arasaka's not on my radar.

entries.femaleVariant: To Arasaka, I'm still worth more alive and well than harmed or dead.
Let us go.
So do your fuckin' job and drive me to North Oak.
It's simple, my life's on the line.
Honestly think I'm runnin' some kinda ruse?
I don't know what to think. But I shall be watching you.
If I can make things right... maybe, just maybe, things'll go back to normal.
entries.maleVariant: If I can make things right... maybe... just maybe things'll go back to normal.

entries.femaleVariant: The Magician.
A person of great talent and charisma, a leader...
Sounds like Johnny.
The card is reversed. That can mean a tendency toward addiction... mental instability.
Oh-ho, OK, definitely Johnny.
The Fool.
Huh, what a surprise…
Let's dig deeper to find its meaning here.
He is one great disturbance.
We'll start with you, V.
The Fool symbolizes the start of a journey, the announcement of something new.
Heh, sounds a lot like the V I first met.
It's the inner child – curious of the world, but also naive and reckless.
The Devil.
Ooh, got another deck lyin' around? A cheerful one?
entries.maleVariant: Got another deck lyin' around? A cheerful one?

entries.femaleVariant: This is no joke, V.
Man, it's good to see your face.
Then we had best not waste any time. We have a long road ahead of us.
Look out for yourself, V.
You too, Misty. And thanks for everything.
Didn't think anything could scare you.
No more hiding in filth, no more second-rate food.
Hey...
We're here to help, OK?
Come on. Everybody's waiting at camp.
OK. And Johnny's?
The Moon...
The cards weren't lying... You've changed.
You really have changed.
And my senses tell me it's for the worse.
All this shit started because I decided to screw over the corp that used to sign my paychecks.
I get it. They're only cards. Always open to interpretation.
I really hope you know what you're doin', V.
Same as me, so stop droning and take me to Hanako.
entries.maleVariant: Yeah, same as me, so stop droning and take me to Hanako.

entries.femaleVariant: Right, Hanako...
Do you remember what last we spoke of?
I do. But I also recall what we spoke of that day.
I'll just put on some music.
Let's see.
Changed my mind. Rather not know.
Actually, Misty, changed my mind.
entries.maleVariant: Ehh, actually, Misty, changed my mind.

entries.femaleVariant: Prolly better I don't know.
Whatever you prefer. I'll put on some music instead.
Some believe uncertainty is an evil that should be dispelled through divination.
The final cards are about your futures.
An inverted Devil symbolizes subjugation, losing control... Aggression. Evil. A power struggle.
Whatever you're planning, treat this as a warning.
Well... that doesn't sound too bad, right?
I don't know, V.
The Moon is mystery.
The Lovers.
Ahh, something that doesn't give me the chills, finally.
entries.maleVariant: Hah, something that doesn't give me the chills, finally.

entries.femaleVariant: The Lovers.
Balance, friendship, love...
OK. And Johnny's?
The Moon...
Well, that... doesn't sound too bad, right?
entries.maleVariant: Well, it... doesn't sound too bad, right?

entries.femaleVariant: I don't know, V.
The Moon is mystery.
Heh, something that doesn't give me the chills, finally.
entries.maleVariant: Phew, something that doesn't give me the chills, finally.

entries.femaleVariant: Balance, friendship, love...
Uh-huh...
V, have you been keeping something from me?
Huh? What? W-why?
You're making a strange face.
Uhh, I-- Ahem. No, no I'm fine.
entries.maleVariant: I, uh... Heheh, ahem. No, I'm fine.

entries.femaleVariant: Though it can also mean difficult choices ahead.
Ain't that the truth.
Mhm. I shall be watching you.
This was my decision. He didn't play a part.
We should go.
Wait a minute.
And now you and this construct have volunteered to sort out things in Arasaka.
Gave you my trust once, Takemura. Now do the same for me.
He may be satisfied.. I will be watching you.
I am sorry to hear this.
Sure.
[Sit]
[Sit]
Just me.
Takin' matters into my own hands.
OK.
And I feel worse.
Others claim it's change that is evil. But that isn't true either. Every minute of every day, we each become someone new.
We shouldn't fear change itself, but only who we might change into. Knowing one's path is most important.
You too.
Take care, Misty. And thanks for everything.
